<h2 class="es-tab-p ">Grammatical gender of nouns denoting professions</h2>		
		
<p>	
Many Russian nouns denoting professions are masculine and they may be used to refer both to men and women. 
It mainly concerns nouns denoting occupations that were once largely dominated by men. 
This is not usual for Russian grammar, since nouns (as well as adjectives and pronouns) should agree in gender with another noun they refer to. 
In conversational Russian, however, such nouns may have feminine forms whose usage is considered to be informal. 
</p>	
	
	
		
		
